FBIS4-47923 "drafr088_d_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-088 Daily Report 5 May 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Malawi Banda Reportedly Suffering From `Leg Problem' Banda Reportedly Suffering From `Leg Problem' EA0505210594 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service in English 1800 GMT 5 May 94 EA0505210594 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania External Service in English 1800 GMT 5 May 94 English BFN [Excerpt] President Kamuzu Banda of Malawi who had brain surgery in South Africa last year has fallen ill again. A newspaper owned by his ruling party reported today that President Kamuzu Banda yesterday failed to attend traditional dances prepared for him at the State House in Lilongwe due to illness. The newspaper quoted the secretary general of the ruling Malawi Congress Party, Mr. Gwanda Chakuamba who presided over the dance ceremony, as saying the elderly leader had a slight leg problem. Government officials were not available for comment. [passage omitted]
